Lord Year 2022, April 25th, Monday

The game's goal is to select two numbers from zero
to one hundred ninetynine to obtain as result the
number one hundred ninetynine.
I do not know is it should be categoryzable as game.
However it opens on the Workbench, it is totally font
sensitive to the windows font and it has the colours
selection.
Clicking with the right mouse button the exit from
the game (?) is optional, it is no more effective.
The second number and the sum number are visible
finally.
Now there is a message that appears when you get the
one hundred ninentynine sum and, to make things more
interesting, now there is the time decreasing, when 
this ends the game ends.
There are three difficulty levels now, Easy, Normal
and Hard.
Under Amikit Real the window's sizes where wrong,
now I should have solved the problem.
Under Amikit for Windows the window's sizes where
wrong again, I hope I have solved the problem now.
At now there is no more to say, I do not know if
someone will like it, it is a pseudo game derivated
from RandomNumbers, one Blitz Basic 2 source code of
mine gifted into the SteMarRegBlitzSources.lha archive.
Now there are two executable, one original from 
Blitz Basic 2 and the other from AmiBlitz3 3.1.0, 
compare them if you want.
Good experimentation!
